{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1047,"text":"I know what you're thinking:"},{"time":3063,"text":"\"Why does that guy get to sit down?\""},{"time":5940,"text":"That's because this is radio."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9097,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12521,"text":"I tell radio stories about design,"},{"time":15494,"text":"and I report on all kinds of stories:"},{"time":17293,"text":"buildings and toothbrushes,\nmascots and wayfinding and fonts."},{"time":21864,"text":"My mission is to get people to engage\nwith the design that they care about"},{"time":25873,"text":"so they begin to pay attention\nto all forms of design."},{"time":29289,"text":"When you decode the world\nwith design intent in mind,"},{"time":33619,"text":"the world becomes kind of magical."},{"time":36044,"text":"Instead of seeing the broken things,"},{"time":38365,"text":"you see all the little bits of genius"},{"time":40666,"text":"that anonymous designers have sweated over\nto make our lives better."},{"time":45170,"text":"And that's essentially\nthe definition of design:"},{"time":47505,"text":"making life better and providing joy."},{"time":51245,"text":"And few things give me greater joy"},{"time":53540,"text":"than a well-designed flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56596,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57770,"text":"Yeah!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59057,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61279,"text":"Happy 50th anniversary\non your flag, Canada."},{"time":63781,"text":"It is beautiful, gold standard."},{"time":66415,"text":"Love it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67772,"text":"I'm kind of obsessed with flags."},{"time":70386,"text":"Sometimes I bring up the topic of flags,"},{"time":72330,"text":"and people are like,\n\"I don't care about flags,\""},{"time":75948,"text":"and then we start talking\nabout flags, and trust me,"},{"time":79294,"text":"100 percent of people care about flags."},{"time":81846,"text":"There's just something about them\nthat works on our emotions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85361,"text":"My family wrapped my Christmas presents\nas flags this year,"},{"time":89412,"text":"including the blue gift bag\nthat's dressed up as the flag of Scotland."},{"time":96192,"text":"I put this picture online,\nand sure enough,"},{"time":98501,"text":"within the first few minutes,\nsomeone left a comment that said,"},{"time":101490,"text":"\"You can take that Scottish Saltire\nand shove it up your ass.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":104969,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":106721,"text":"See, people are passionate\nabout flags, you know?"},{"time":109043,"text":"That's the way it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110361,"text":"What I love about flags"},{"time":111924,"text":"is that once you understand\nthe design of flags,"},{"time":114219,"text":"what makes a good flag,\nwhat makes a bad flag,"},{"time":116813,"text":"you can understand\nthe design of almost anything."},{"time":119396,"text":"So what I'm going to do here is,"},{"time":121207,"text":"I cracked open an episode\nof my radio show,"},{"time":124767,"text":"\"99% Invisible,\" and I'm going\nto reconstruct it here on stage,"},{"time":127861,"text":"so when I press a button over here --"},{"time":130151,"text":"Voice: S for Sound --"},{"time":132050,"text":"Roman Mars: It's going to make a sound,"},{"time":133975,"text":"and so whenever you hear a sound\nor a voice or a piece of music,"},{"time":137064,"text":"it's because I pressed a button."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138775,"text":"Voice: Sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140879,"text":"RM: All right, got it? Here we go."},{"time":144719,"text":"Three, two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147825,"text":"This is 99% Invisible. I'm Roman Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154944,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156969,"text":"Narrator: The five basic\nprinciples of flag design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159599,"text":"Roman Mars: According to the North\nAmerican Vexillological Association."},{"time":163129,"text":"Vexillological."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164959,"text":"Ted Kaye: Vexillology\nis the study of flags."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168029,"text":"RM: It's that extra \"lol\"\nthat makes it sound weird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170485,"text":"Narrator: Number one, keep it simple."},{"time":172403,"text":"The flag should be so simple\nthat a child can draw it from memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175712,"text":"RM: Before I moved to Chicago in 2005,"},{"time":177687,"text":"I didn't even know cities\nhad their own flags."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180211,"text":"TK: Most larger cities do have flags."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182112,"text":"RM: Well, I didn't know that,\nthat's Ted Kaye, by the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184865,"text":"TK: Hello."},{"time":186064,"text":"RM: He's a flag expert,\nhe's a totally awesome guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188498,"text":"TK: I'm Ted Kaye, I have edited\na scholarly journal on flag studies,"},{"time":191737,"text":"and I am currently involved\nwith the Portland Flag Association"},{"time":194735,"text":"and the North American\nVexillological Association."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198122,"text":"RM: Ted literally wrote\nthe book on flag design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201123,"text":"Narrator: \"Good Flag, Bad Flag.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":202675,"text":"RM: It's more of a pamphlet, really,\nit's about 16 pages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205395,"text":"TK: Yes, it's called \"Good Flag, Bad Flag:\nHow to Design a Great Flag.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":209328,"text":"RM: And that first city flag\nI discovered in Chicago"},{"time":212047,"text":"is a beaut:"},{"time":213318,"text":"white field, two horizontal blue stripes,"},{"time":216867,"text":"and four six-pointed red stars\ndown the middle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219752,"text":"(Sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221314,"text":"Narrator: Number two,\nuse meaningful symbolism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223599,"text":"TK: The blue stripes represent\nthe water, the river and the lake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226675,"text":"Narrator: The flag's images,\ncolors or pattern"},{"time":228903,"text":"should relate to what it symbolizes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230650,"text":"TK: The red stars represent\nsignificant events in Chicago's history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234459,"text":"RM: Namely, the founding of Fort Dearborn\non the future site of Chicago,"},{"time":238187,"text":"the Great Chicago Fire,"},{"time":241046,"text":"the World Columbian Exposition,\nwhich everyone remembers"},{"time":243717,"text":"because of the White City,"},{"time":245535,"text":"and the Century of Progress Exposition,\nwhich no one remembers at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250433,"text":"Narrator: Number three,\nuse two to three basic colors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252986,"text":"TK: The basic rule for colors\nis to use two to three colors"},{"time":256478,"text":"from the standard color set:\nred, white, blue, green, yellow and black."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261926,"text":"RM: The design of the Chicago flag\nhas complete buy-in"},{"time":264492,"text":"with an entire cross-section of the city."},{"time":266483,"text":"It is everywhere;"},{"time":267675,"text":"every municipal building flies the flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270263,"text":"Whet Moser: There's probably\nat least one store on every block"},{"time":273220,"text":"near where I work that sells\nsome sort of Chicago flag paraphernalia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276487,"text":"RM: That's Whet Moser\nfrom Chicago magazine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278918,"text":"WM: Today, just for example,\nI went to get a haircut,"},{"time":281935,"text":"and when I sat down in the barber's chair,"},{"time":284333,"text":"there was a Chicago flag on the box\nthat the barber kept all his tools in,"},{"time":288804,"text":"and then in the mirror, there was\na Chicago flag on the wall behind me."},{"time":292287,"text":"When I left, a guy passed me who had\na Chicago flag badge on his backpack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297279,"text":"RM: It's adaptable and remixable."},{"time":299366,"text":"The six-pointed stars in particular\nshow up in all kinds of places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302955,"text":"WM: The coffee I bought the other day\nhad a Chicago star on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306660,"text":"RM: It's a distinct symbol\nof Chicago pride."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309655,"text":"TK: When a police officer\nor a firefighter dies in Chicago,"},{"time":313376,"text":"often it's not the flag\nof the United States on his casket."},{"time":316990,"text":"It can be the flag of the city of Chicago."},{"time":319912,"text":"That's how deeply the flag has gotten\ninto the civic imagery of Chicago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325566,"text":"RM: And it isn't just that people\nlove Chicago and therefore love the flag."},{"time":329275,"text":"I also think that people love Chicago more\nbecause the flag is so cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335154,"text":"TK: A positive feedback loop there\nbetween great symbolism and civic pride."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340278,"text":"RM: OK, so when I moved back\nto San Francisco in 2008,"},{"time":343532,"text":"I researched its flag,"},{"time":344925,"text":"because I had never seen it\nin the previous eight years I lived there."},{"time":350027,"text":"And I found it, I am sorry to say,"},{"time":352935,"text":"sadly lacking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355211,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358345,"text":"I know."},{"time":360528,"text":"It hurts me, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361796,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364643,"text":"TK: Well, let me start from the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366410,"text":"Narrator: Number one, keep it simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368220,"text":"TK: Keeping it simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369420,"text":"Narrator: The flag should be so simple\nthat a child can draw it from memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373018,"text":"TK: It's a relatively complex flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374911,"text":"RM: OK, here we go, OK."},{"time":376203,"text":"The main component\nof the San Francisco flag is a phoenix"},{"time":378912,"text":"representing the city\nrising from the ashes"},{"time":381145,"text":"after the devastating fires of the 1850s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384211,"text":"TK: A powerful symbol for San Francisco."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386995,"text":"RM: I still don't really dig the phoenix."},{"time":388994,"text":"Design-wise, it manages\nto both be too crude"},{"time":391664,"text":"and have too many details\nat the same time,"},{"time":394500,"text":"which if you were trying for that,"},{"time":396215,"text":"you wouldn't be able to do it,"},{"time":398156,"text":"and it just looks bad at a distance,"},{"time":399930,"text":"but having deep meaning\nputs that element in the plus column."},{"time":403622,"text":"Behind the phoenix,\nthe background is mostly white,"},{"time":406846,"text":"and then it has a substantial\ngold border around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410175,"text":"TK: Which is a very attractive\ndesign element."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413295,"text":"RM: I think it's OK, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":414617,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":416200,"text":"here come the big no-nos of flag design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419220,"text":"Narrator: Number four,\nno lettering or seals."},{"time":421641,"text":"Never use writing of any kind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423901,"text":"RM: Underneath the phoenix,\nthere's a motto on a ribbon"},{"time":426523,"text":"that translates to\n\"Gold in peace, iron in war,\""},{"time":429502,"text":"plus -- and this is the big problem --"},{"time":431857,"text":"it says San Francisco across the bottom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435090,"text":"TK: If you need to write the name\nof what you're representing on your flag,"},{"time":438949,"text":"your symbolism has failed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440749,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442549,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444577,"text":"RM: The United States flag\ndoesn't say \"USA\" across the front."},{"time":448542,"text":"In fact, country flags,\nthey tend to behave."},{"time":451723,"text":"Like, hats off to South Africa\nand Turkey and Israel"},{"time":455034,"text":"and Somalia and Japan and Gambia."},{"time":457186,"text":"There's a bunch\nof really great country flags,"},{"time":459728,"text":"but they obey good design principles\nbecause the stakes are high."},{"time":463983,"text":"They're on the international stage."},{"time":466404,"text":"But city, state and regional flags\nare another story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471058,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472975,"text":"There is a scourge of bad flags --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":475731,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476800,"text":"and they must be stopped."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478332,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":479515,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":480761,"text":"That is the truth and that is the dare."},{"time":484385,"text":"The first step is to recognize\nthat we have a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488268,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":492586,"text":"A lot of people tend to think\nthat good design"},{"time":495333,"text":"is just a matter of taste,"},{"time":496694,"text":"and quite honestly,\nsometimes it is, actually,"},{"time":499740,"text":"but sometimes it isn't, all right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":502145,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503747,"text":"Here's the full list of NAVA\nflag design principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508328,"text":"Narrator: The five\nbasic principles of flag design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511006,"text":"Narrator: Number one.\nTK: Keep it simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513626,"text":"Narrator: Number two.\nTK: Use meaningful symbolism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516078,"text":"Narrator: Number three.\nTK: Use two to three basic colors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518849,"text":"Narrator: Number four.\nTK: No lettering or seals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521169,"text":"Narrator: Never use writing of any kind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523125,"text":"TK: Because you can't\nread that at a distance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525341,"text":"Narrator: Number five.\nTK: And be distinctive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527528,"text":"RM: All the best flags tend\nto stick to these principles."},{"time":530226,"text":"And like I said before,\nmost country flags are OK."},{"time":532600,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":533786,"text":"if you showed this list of principles\nto any designer of almost anything,"},{"time":537302,"text":"they would say these principles --\nsimplicity, deep meaning,"},{"time":540153,"text":"having few colors\nor being thoughtful about colors,"},{"time":542907,"text":"uniqueness, don't have\nwriting you can't read --"},{"time":545183,"text":"all those principles apply to them, too."},{"time":547781,"text":"But sadly, good design principles\nare rarely invoked in US city flags."},{"time":552876,"text":"Our biggest problem\nseems to be that fourth one."},{"time":555387,"text":"We just can't stop ourselves\nfrom putting our names on our flags,"},{"time":559520,"text":"or little municipal seals\nwith tiny writing on them."},{"time":563415,"text":"Here's the thing about municipal seals:"},{"time":565343,"text":"They were designed\nto be on pieces of paper"},{"time":568128,"text":"where you can read them,"},{"time":569356,"text":"not on flags 100 feet away\nflapping in the breeze."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572533,"text":"So here's a bunch of flags again."},{"time":574428,"text":"Vexillologists call these SOBs:"},{"time":577640,"text":"Seals on a bedsheet --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":579082,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580278,"text":"and if you can't tell\nwhat city they go to,"},{"time":583180,"text":"yeah, that's exactly the problem,"},{"time":585071,"text":"except for Anaheim,\napparently, they fixed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588043,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":591208,"text":"These flags are everywhere in the US."},{"time":593565,"text":"The European equivalent\nof the municipal seal"},{"time":595758,"text":"is the city coat of arms ..."},{"time":598368,"text":"and this is where we can learn\na lesson for how to do things right."},{"time":601573,"text":"So this is the city\ncoat of arms of Amsterdam."},{"time":603774,"text":"Now, if this were a United States city,"},{"time":605814,"text":"the flag would probably look like this."},{"time":608062,"text":"You know, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609264,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":610521,"text":"But instead, the flag of Amsterdam"},{"time":612595,"text":"looks like this."},{"time":615546,"text":"Rather than plopping\nthe whole coat of arms"},{"time":617989,"text":"on a solid background and writing\n\"Amsterdam\" below it,"},{"time":621184,"text":"they just take the key elements\nof the escutcheon, the shield,"},{"time":624117,"text":"and they turn it into the most\nbadass city flag in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627688,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629442,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":633794,"text":"And because it's so badass,"},{"time":636030,"text":"those flags and crosses\nare found throughout Amsterdam,"},{"time":638763,"text":"just like Chicago, they're used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641955,"text":"Even though seal-on-a-bedsheet flags\nare particularly painful"},{"time":644892,"text":"and offensive to me,"},{"time":646161,"text":"nothing can quite prepare you"},{"time":648764,"text":"for one of the biggest train wrecks\nin vexillological history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651869,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":653137,"text":"Are you ready?"},{"time":654815,"text":"It's the flag of Milwaukee, Wisconsin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657594,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":665465,"text":"I mean, it's distinctive,"},{"time":669459,"text":"I'll give them that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672114,"text":"Steve Kodis: It was adopted in 1955."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674791,"text":"RM: The city ran a contest"},{"time":676094,"text":"and gathered a bunch of submissions\nwith all kinds of designs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679513,"text":"SK: And an alderman\nby the name of Fred Steffan"},{"time":683744,"text":"cobbled together parts of the submissions\nto make what is now the Milwaukee flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690980,"text":"RM: It's a kitchen sink flag."},{"time":693069,"text":"There's a gigantic gear\nrepresenting industry,"},{"time":695905,"text":"there's a ship recognizing the port,"},{"time":698180,"text":"a giant stalk of wheat"},{"time":699713,"text":"paying homage to the brewing industry."},{"time":701803,"text":"It's a hot mess,"},{"time":703517,"text":"and Steve Kodis, a graphic designer\nfrom Milwaukee, wants to change it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708368,"text":"SK: It's really awful."},{"time":709964,"text":"It's a misstep on the city's behalf,"},{"time":713411,"text":"to say the least."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715617,"text":"RM: But what puts\nthe Milwaukee flag over the top,"},{"time":718059,"text":"almost to the point of self-parody,"},{"time":720163,"text":"is on it is a picture of the Civil War\nbattle flag of the Milwaukee regiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726109,"text":"SK: So that's the final element in it"},{"time":728439,"text":"that just makes it\nthat much more ridiculous,"},{"time":730850,"text":"that there is a flag design\nwithin the Milwaukee flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735549,"text":"RM: On the flag. Yeah. Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737642,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738831,"text":"Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740161,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":741893,"text":"Now, Milwaukee is a fantastic city."},{"time":744308,"text":"I've been there, I love it."},{"time":746583,"text":"The most depressing part\nof this flag, though,"},{"time":748883,"text":"is that there have been\ntwo major redesign contests."},{"time":752004,"text":"The last one was held in 2001."},{"time":754199,"text":"105 entries were received."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756773,"text":"TK: But in the end, the members\nof the Milwaukee Arts Board"},{"time":759565,"text":"decided that none of the new entries\nwere worthy of flying over the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763118,"text":"RM: They couldn't agree\nto change that thing!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":765522,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":766775,"text":"That's discouraging enough\nto make you think"},{"time":768861,"text":"that good design and democracy\njust simply do not go together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772284,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":773462,"text":"But Steve Kotas is going\nto try one more time"},{"time":776315,"text":"to redesign the Milwaukee flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779188,"text":"SK: I believe Milwaukee is a great city."},{"time":781173,"text":"Every great city deserves a great flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784325,"text":"RM: Steve isn't ready\nto reveal his design yet."},{"time":786575,"text":"One of the things about\nproposing one of these things"},{"time":789121,"text":"is you have to get people on board,"},{"time":790817,"text":"and then you reveal your design."},{"time":792407,"text":"But here's the trick:"},{"time":793721,"text":"If you want to design a great flag,"},{"time":795433,"text":"a kick-ass flag like Chicago's or DC's,\nwhich also has a great flag,"},{"time":799298,"text":"start by drawing\na one-by-one-and-a-half-inch rectangle"},{"time":802160,"text":"on a piece of paper."},{"time":803528,"text":"Your design has to fit\nwithin that tiny rectangle."},{"time":806050,"text":"Here's why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807288,"text":"TK: A three-by-five-foot flag\non a pole 100 feet away"},{"time":812350,"text":"looks about the same size\nas a one-by-one-and-a-half-inch rectangle"},{"time":818995,"text":"seen about 15 inches from your eye."},{"time":821598,"text":"You'd be surprised by how compelling\nand simple the design can be"},{"time":825759,"text":"when you hold yourself to that limitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829102,"text":"RM: Meanwhile, back in San Francisco."},{"time":831886,"text":"Is there anything we can do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":834697,"text":"TK: I like to say that in every bad flag\nthere's a good flag trying to get out."},{"time":838671,"text":"The way to make\nSan Francisco's flag a good flag"},{"time":841143,"text":"is to take the motto off\nbecause you can't read that at a distance."},{"time":844698,"text":"Take the name off,"},{"time":846226,"text":"and the border might even be made thicker,\nso it's more a part of the flag."},{"time":850483,"text":"And I would simply take the phoenix"},{"time":852360,"text":"and make it a great big element\nin the middle of the flag."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855761,"text":"RM: But the current phoenix,\nthat's got to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858606,"text":"TK: I would simplify\nor stylize the phoenix."},{"time":862036,"text":"Depict a big, wide-winged bird"},{"time":864295,"text":"coming out of flames."},{"time":865952,"text":"Emphasize those flames."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867779,"text":"RM: So this San Francisco flag\nwas designed by Frank Chimero"},{"time":870646,"text":"based on Ted Kaye's suggestions."},{"time":872208,"text":"I don't know what he would do\nif we was completely unfettered"},{"time":875091,"text":"and didn't follow those guidelines."},{"time":876799,"text":"Fans of my radio show and podcast,\nheard me complain about bad flags."},{"time":880089,"text":"They've sent me other suggested designs."},{"time":882036,"text":"This one's by Neil Mussett."},{"time":883819,"text":"Both are so much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886887,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888339,"text":"And I think if they were adopted,"},{"time":890292,"text":"I would see them around the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893135,"text":"In my crusade to make\nflags of the world more beautiful,"},{"time":896353,"text":"many listeners have taken it\nupon themselves"},{"time":898473,"text":"to redesign their flags\nand look into the feasibility"},{"time":900983,"text":"of getting them officially adopted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903039,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904316,"text":"If you see your city flag and like it,"},{"time":906971,"text":"fly it,"},{"time":908213,"text":"even if it violates a design rule or two."},{"time":910287,"text":"I don't care."},{"time":911682,"text":"But if you don't see your city flag,"},{"time":913866,"text":"maybe it doesn't exist, but maybe it does,"},{"time":917060,"text":"and it just sucks,"},{"time":918400,"text":"and I dare you to join the effort\nto try to change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923867,"text":"As we move more and more into cities,"},{"time":926483,"text":"the city flag will become\nnot just a symbol of that city as a place,"},{"time":931402,"text":"but also, it could become a symbol\nof how that city considers design itself,"},{"time":937709,"text":"especially today, as the populace\nis becoming more design-aware."},{"time":940958,"text":"And I think design awareness\nis at an all-time high."},{"time":943990,"text":"A well-designed flag could be seen\nas an indicator of how a city"},{"time":948045,"text":"considers all of its design systems:"},{"time":950674,"text":"its public transit,"},{"time":952306,"text":"its parks, its signage."},{"time":954303,"text":"It might seem frivolous, but it's not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":957857,"text":"TK: Often when city leaders say,"},{"time":959717,"text":"\"We have more important things to do\nthan worry about a city flag,\""},{"time":964217,"text":"my response is,"},{"time":965840,"text":"\"If you had a great city flag,"},{"time":967444,"text":"you would have a banner\nfor people to rally under"},{"time":970184,"text":"to face those more important things.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":973781,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":974955,"text":"RM: I've seen firsthand\nwhat a good city flag can do"},{"time":977411,"text":"in the case of Chicago."},{"time":978724,"text":"The marriage of good design\nand civic pride"},{"time":981335,"text":"is something that we need in all places."},{"time":983851,"text":"The best part about municipal flags\nis that we own them."},{"time":987727,"text":"They are an open-source,"},{"time":989302,"text":"publicly owned design language\nof the community."},{"time":992991,"text":"When they are done well,"},{"time":994408,"text":"they are remixable, adaptable,\nand they are powerful."},{"time":998677,"text":"We could control the branding\nand graphical imagery"},{"time":1001116,"text":"of our cities with a good flag,"},{"time":1002740,"text":"but instead, by having\nbad flags we don't use,"},{"time":1005439,"text":"we cede that territory to sports teams"},{"time":1008409,"text":"and chambers of commerce\nand tourism boards."},{"time":1010836,"text":"Sports teams can leave\nand break our hearts."},{"time":1013357,"text":"And besides, some of us\ndon't really care about sports."},{"time":1016465,"text":"And tourism campaigns can just be cheesy."},{"time":1019725,"text":"But a great city flag"},{"time":1021272,"text":"is something that represents\na city to its people"},{"time":1023686,"text":"and its people to the world at large."},{"time":1025869,"text":"And when that flag is a beautiful thing,"},{"time":1028328,"text":"that connection is a beautiful thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031219,"text":"So maybe all the city flags\ncan be as inspiring as Hong Kong"},{"time":1034721,"text":"or Portland or Trondheim,"},{"time":1036897,"text":"and we can do away with all the bad flags"},{"time":1038904,"text":"like San Francisco, Milwaukee,\nCedar Rapids,"},{"time":1042827,"text":"and finally, when we're all done,"},{"time":1045490,"text":"we can do something\nabout Pocatello, Idaho,"},{"time":1048329,"text":"considered by the North American\nVexillological Association"},{"time":1052050,"text":"as the worst city flag in North America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1056179,"text":"[Proud to be Pocatello]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057370,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059950,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063896,"text":"Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1065071,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066372,"text":"That thing has a trademark\nsymbol on it, people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068901,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070940,"text":"That hurts me just to look at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072652,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073915,"text":"Thank you so much for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075860,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081966,"text":"[Music by: Melodium (@melodiumbox)\nand Keegan DeWitt (@keegandewitt)]"}]}]}